<Section Background="#FFFA8072" xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation" xmlns:s="clr-namespace:System;assembly=mscorlib" xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">
  <Table CellSpacing="5">
    <Table.Columns>
      <TableColumn />
      <TableColumn Style="{DynamicResource ColumnStyle1}" />
    </Table.Columns>
    <Table.Resources>
      <Style TargetType="TableCell" x:Key="CellStyle1">
        <Style.Resources>
          <ResourceDictionary />
        </Style.Resources>
        <Setter Property="TextElement.FontFamily">
          
            <FontFamily>Verdana</FontFamily>
          
        </Setter>
        <Setter Property="TextElement.FontWeight">
          
            <FontWeight>Bold</FontWeight>
          
        </Setter>
        <Setter Property="TextElement.Foreground">
          
            <SolidColorBrush>#FFFF0000</SolidColorBrush>
          
        </Setter>
        <Setter Property="TextElement.FontStyle">
          
            <FontStyle>Italic</FontStyle>
          
        </Setter>
        <Setter Property="TableCell.ColumnSpan">
          
            <s:Int32>2</s:Int32>
          
        </Setter>
      </Style>
      <Style TargetType="TableColumn" x:Key="ColumnStyle1">
        <Style.Resources>
          <ResourceDictionary />
        </Style.Resources>
        <Setter Property="TableColumn.Width">
          
            <GridLength>150</GridLength>
          
        </Setter>
      </Style>
      <Style TargetType="TableRowGroup" x:Key="RowGroupStyle1">
        <Style.Resources>
          <ResourceDictionary />
        </Style.Resources>
        <Setter Property="TextElement.Background">
          
            <SolidColorBrush>#FFD2B48C</SolidColorBrush>
          
        </Setter>
      </Style>
      <Style TargetType="TableRow" x:Key="RowStyle1">
        <Style.Resources>
          <ResourceDictionary />
        </Style.Resources>
        <Setter Property="TextElement.Foreground">
          
            <SolidColorBrush>#FFFFFFFF</SolidColorBrush>
          
        </Setter>
      </Style>
      <Style TargetType="FlowDocument" x:Key="{x:Type FlowDocument}">
        <Style.Resources>
          <ResourceDictionary />
        </Style.Resources>
        <Setter Property="TextElement.Foreground">
          
            <SolidColorBrush>#FF0000FF</SolidColorBrush>
          
        </Setter>
        <Setter Property="TextElement.FontFamily">
          
            <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
          
        </Setter>
        <Setter Property="TextElement.FontSize">
          
            <s:Double>20</s:Double>
          
        </Setter>
      </Style>
      <Style TargetType="TableCell" x:Key="{x:Type TableCell}">
        <Style.Resources>
          <ResourceDictionary />
        </Style.Resources>
        <Setter Property="TextElement.FontFamily">
          
            <FontFamily>Comic Sans MS</FontFamily>
          
        </Setter>
        <Setter Property="TextElement.FontSize">
          
            <s:Double>16</s:Double>
          
        </Setter>
        <Setter Property="Block.BorderThickness">
          
            <Thickness>1,1,1,1</Thickness>
          
        </Setter>
        <Setter Property="Block.BorderBrush">
          
            <SolidColorBrush>#FF008000</SolidColorBrush>
          
        </Setter>
      </Style>
    </Table.Resources>
    <TableRowGroup Style="{DynamicResource RowGroupStyle1}">
      <TableRow>
        <TableCell FontSize="13.3333333333333" Foreground="#FFFFFF00" Padding="4,4,4,4" FontFamily="Arial">
          <Paragraph>Can Ganguly lift India from Down Under?</Paragraph>
        </TableCell>
        <TableCell FontSize="13.3333333333333" Foreground="#FFFFFF00" Padding="4,4,4,4" FontFamily="Arial">
          <Paragraph>Column 2</Paragraph>
        </TableCell>
      </TableRow>
    </TableRowGroup>
    <TableRowGroup>
      <TableRow>
        <TableCell>
          <Paragraph>NEW DELHI: India's skipper Sourav Ganguly could not have timed his return to the team any better. <FlowDocumentScrollViewer><FlowDocument><Paragraph>This is a big week for Indian cricket with big matches against Australia and New Zealand.</Paragraph></FlowDocument></FlowDocumentScrollViewer>There is of course the added chance of India crashing out of the series if they botch up both of their matches.</Paragraph>
        </TableCell>
        <TableCell Foreground="#FFFFFF00" Padding="4,4,4,4">
          <Paragraph>Column 2</Paragraph>
        </TableCell>
      </TableRow>
      <TableRow>
        <TableCell Style="{DynamicResource CellStyle1}">
          <Paragraph>Australia top the points table with 23 points, comprising four wins in a row. The Kiwis have 10 points from five matches while India are on nine from four matches.<LineBreak />With Australia already assured of a berth in the finals, the Bangalore match is only of academic value. India has to win against New Zealand at Hyderabad on Saturday to book a place in the final to be played at Kolkata on November 18.</Paragraph>
        </TableCell>
      </TableRow>
      <TableRow Style="{DynamicResource RowStyle1}">
        <TableCell>
          <Paragraph>The HR Intranet provides general information and guidelines only. It does not create any contractual rights or guarantee specific treatment in any given situation.</Paragraph>
        </TableCell>
        <TableCell FontSize="13.3333333333333" Foreground="#FFFFFF00" Padding="4,4,4,4" FontFamily="Arial">
          <Paragraph>Column 2</Paragraph>
        </TableCell>
      </TableRow>
    </TableRowGroup>
  </Table>
</Section>